Set 26 
Collection “orderinfo“ which contains the documents given as below 
{  
cust_id:123  
cust_name:”abc”,  
status:”A”,  
price:250  
}  
1) find the average price for each customers having status 'A'  
2) Display the status of the customers whose amount/price lie between 100 and 1000  
3) Display the customers information without “_id” .  
4) create a simple index on onderinfo collection and fire the queries.



use orderdb

db.createCollection("orderinfo")

db.orderinfo.insertMany([
{
cust_id:123,
cust_name:"abc",
status:"A",
price:250
},
{
cust_id:124,
cust_name:"om",
status:"B",
price:500
},
{
cust_id:125,
cust_name:"krushna",
status:"A",
price:700
}
])

// 1. Average price for status A

db.orderinfo.aggregate([
{
$match:{status:"A"}
},
{
$group:{
_id:null,
avg_price:{$avg:"$price"}
}
}
])

// 2. Display customers whose price is between 100 and 1000

db.orderinfo.find(
{
price:{
$gte:100,
$lte:1000
}
}
)

// 3. Display customer information without _id

db.orderinfo.find(
{},
{
_id:0
}
)

// 4. Create index

db.orderinfo.createIndex(
{
cust_name:1
}
)
